.TH "thermal_zone_get_temp" 9 "thermal_zone_get_temp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
thermal_zone_get_temp \- returns the temperature of a thermal zone
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" thermal_zone_get_temp
.BI "(struct thermal_zone_device *tz "  ","
.BI "int *temp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tz" 12
a valid pointer to a struct thermal_zone_device
.IP "temp" 12
a valid pointer to where to store the resulting temperature.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When a valid thermal zone reference is passed, it will fetch its
temperature and fill \fItemp\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
On success returns 0, an error code otherwise
